    "description": "This should allow you to do:\r\n\r\nnosetests -c nose.cfg\r\n\r\nand run all the tests.  Additionally, yt.testing.test() should run the yt tests.\r\n\r\nIn the future, this will allow us to mark some items as \"slow\" or requiring reference answers.  I think this will enable better integration with answer testing.\r\n\r\nOne thing I'm not sure about is if there's any way to have nosetests when run without arguments check nose.cfg in the current directory.  I don't think there is.  Anybody else know?",
